<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TURBOCHARGERS - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" id="hl1050202" graphiccount="7">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>CARE MUST BE TAKEN DURING HANDLING OF IMPELLER AND TURBINE WHEEL. BE VERY CAREFUL AND AVOID,
                    BENDING ANY BLADES. BENT BLADES MUST NEVER BE USED.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) bearings and spacer onto turbine shaft (
                <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050223">2.23</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide shroud and turbine wheel shaft into center housing (
                <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050224">2.24</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reassemble center housing as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place an O-Ring onto compressor housing.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install four (4) bolts securing center housing backplate. Tighten to special torque
                    value. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050225">2.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050223" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3105" filename="../figeg3/EG3105.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.23.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Turbine Wheel and Shaft</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Bearings and Spacer</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050224" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3104" filename="../figeg3/EG3104.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.24.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Center Housing</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Turbine Wheel Shroud</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Turbine Wheel and Shaft</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050225" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3102" filename="../figeg3/EG3102.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.25.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Compressor Housing Backplate</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Compressor Housing Backplate</callout1>
                        <callout1>Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install compressor wheel onto turbine wheel shaft. Tighten to special torque value.
                    Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050226">2.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If turbocharger is equipped with a wastegate, perform steps 4, 5 and 6. If turbocharger is
                            not equipped with a wastegate, proceed onto step 7.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install wastegate actuator bracket with actuator arm and diaphragm attached to center
                housing. Secure with three (3) bolts. Tighten to standard torque. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050227">2.27</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050226" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3108" filename="../figeg3/EG3108.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>FIGURE 2.26.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Impeller Wheel</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Center Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Compressor Housing Backplate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050227" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3113" filename="../figeg3/EG3113.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>FIGURE 2.27.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Wastegate Actuator Arm</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Wastegate Bracket Mounting Bolts (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Wastegate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wastegate actuator arm to wastegate and install retaining clip.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align marks and attach wastegate housing to turbine housing and secure with six (6) bolts.
                Tighten to special torque. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050228">2.28</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach turbine housing to center housing. Secure with four (4) bolts and tighten to special
                torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align marks and attach compressor housing to backplate.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using six (6) bolts and two (2) clamps secure compressor housing to backplate. Tighten to
                special torque value. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050229">2.29</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>USE A NEW ACTUATOR HOSE WHEN REASSEMBLING TURBOCHARGER.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Attach hose from the compressor side of the turbocharger to the wastegate actuator. Secure
                hose with two (2) hose clamps.
                <emph type="bold">If Equipped.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050228" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3111" filename="../figeg3/EG3111.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>FIGURE 2.28.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Wastegate Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Turbine Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Wastegate Housing Mounting Bolts (6)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050229" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3112" filename="../figeg3/EG3112.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>FIGURE 2.29.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Wastegate Actuator</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Actuator Hose</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Compressor Housing Mounting Bolt (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Compressor Housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
